From: Tomaz Zaman <tomaz@mono.si>
Date: Tue, 28 Apr 2026 21:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fmc: ASK extensions (shared schemes, port ID, external/aging hashtables)

Add support for:
- Port ID (portid) field in port configuration output
- Shared scheme support with CC/HT node replication
- Fix PPPoE nextp field name (NET_HEADER_FIELD_PPPoE_PID)
- external="yes" attribute on <hashtable> XML nodes
  (pushes hash buckets off MURAM into DDR-backed USDPAA memory)
- aging="yes" attribute on <hashtable> XML nodes
- data_mem_id / data_liodn_offs hashtable attributes
  (gated DPAA_VERSION>=11; LS1046A: -DLS1043 path)

These extensions are required for the CMM daemon and fast path offload
functionality on the Mono Gateway. The external/aging additions resolve
PCD apply rc=65280 caused by FMan internal MURAM (384 KiB) being too
small to host all hash buckets for typical Mono PCD configurations.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [vendor-specific extension]
Signed-off-by: Tomaz Zaman <tomaz@mono.si>
---
